    "created_at": "2012-05-30T01:16:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-05-30T01:16:32Z",
    "body": "This looks good, but I would like to do this in a slightly different way. Instead of creating command line flags can we just create lint checks called 'all' and 'err-all'? That way they can also be activated via the crate `warn` attributes (`#[warn(all)]`). The lint pass itself can interpret 'all', 'no_all' and 'err_all' specially to flip all the checks on/off, etc.\n\nIn general we want compile options to be specified via attributes, and only secondarily via the command line.\n",
